  "body": "<!-- Please use this template while reporting a bug and provide as much info as possible. Not doing so may result in your bug not being addressed in a timely manner. Thanks!\r\n\r\nIf the matter is security related, please disclose it privately via https://kubernetes.io/security/\r\n-->\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nAzure cloud provider Instances interfaces don't work expected on Windows containers. This is because Windows containers don't support HostNetwork mode, while Azure cloud provider depends on \"os.Hostname()\" to check whether the VMName from IMDS is same with NodeName:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/84dc7046797aad80f258b6740a98e79199c8bb4d/staging/src/k8s.io/legacy-cloud-providers/azure/azure_instances.go#L233-L246\r\n\r\nTo fix it, the dependency on Hostname should be removed.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n- OS (e.g: `cat /etc/os-release`):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Network plugin and version (if this is a network-related bug):\r\n- Others:\r\n\r\n/sig cloud-provider\r\n/priority critical-urgent\r\n/area provider/azure\r\n/milestone v1.18",
